inged creatures at the entrance to the garden and a flaming, flashing sword to guard the way to the life-giving tree. "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"Then at the east side of the garden he put living creatures and a flaming sword which turned in all directions. This was to keep anyone from coming near the tree that gives life. "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"He drove man out and stationed the cherubim and the flaming, whirling sword east of the garden of Eden to guard the way to the tree of life. "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"After he had expelled the man, the LORD God placed winged angels at the eastern end of the garden of Eden, along with a fiery, turning sword, to prevent access to the tree of life."}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"When he drove the man out, he placed on the eastern side of the orchard in Eden angelic sentries who used the flame of a whirling sword to guard the way to the tree of life. "}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"So he drove out the man; and he stationed the cherubim at the east of the garden of Eden, and a flaming sword which turned every direction, to guard the way to the tree of life."}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"After he sent the man out, God placed angels and a flaming sword that turned in all directions east of the Garden of Eden. He placed them there to guard the way to the tree of life. "}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"So He drove out the man; and He placed at the east of the garden of Eden the cherubim, and the flaming sword which turned every way, to keep the way to the tree of life."}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"So He drove the man out; and at the east of the garden of Eden He stationed the cherubim, and the flaming sword which turned every direction, to guard the way to the tree of life."}, {:version=>"King James 2000 Bible", :text=>"So he drove out the man; and he placed at the east of the 